cs.SI, cs.DL, cs.CY, cs.SD, cs.IR

The paper analyzes a citation network and develops a network-based model to understand the impact of exponential growth on the underlying knowledge network. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.SD (Software Engineering), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). However, given the focus on citation analysis and the attention economy in science, cs.SI and cs.DL are the most likely sub-categories.
